Key Match Events: Atlanta Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title with a 4-1 win over the Philadelphia Phillies
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Brian Snitker said, 'We’ve checked one box.'
The Braves took special satisfaction in clinching on the same Citizens Bank Park field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves are on pace to finish with 106 wins, which would tie the 1998 Braves for the most wins in the franchise’s nearly 150-year history.
Others: The Braves are off as they head to Florida for a three-game set with the Marlins. The Braves send RHP Bryce Elder (12-4, 3.38 ERA) to the mound. The Marlins have not named a starter.
